      <p>That is so cool! You picked something very very very common in northern germany (Hamburg and Bremen). In the cold times we cook kale alle the time (together with potatoes and pinkel (which is a special &#8220;has to go with kale&#8221;- sausage).</>We also have a nice little convention: to go for a loooong walk in the cold (best: snow!), drink loads of schnapps (which is carried in a little transport wagon). And after that: eat tons of kale with pinkel.</>At the end of the day, the kaleking (really!!) is pronounced.</>Nice rite.</p>
