    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>More than any other site I am regularly inspired to try your recipes. Thanks! I&#8217;m going to try this with collard greens that are in my fridge.</></>On kale &#8211; this year I finally found a use for it other than kale/potato/sausage soup. I boil it until soft, drain, chop thinly, chill, drizzle with sesame oil, seasoned rice vinegar, siracha &#8211; voila &#8211; Kale Salad Seaweed Style. Fancy it up with a sprinkle of sesame seeds. Yum.</p>
