    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have been OBSESSED with cavolo nero ever since i saw tried the cavolo nero bruscetta from the River Cafe Cookbook.  but I have also been consuming it raw.  It&#8217;s quite delicious and surprisingly tender cut into 1 inch strips and tossed with olive oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and plenty of parmesan reggiano.  If you let the salad sit for 15 minutes after tossing, the dressing works miracles on the leaves.</p>
