  <li id="comment-12969" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.asiarooms.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Sujan Patricia</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/10/pleasantly-sogged/#comment-12969"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-02-10T06:26:00-05:00">Tuesday, February 10, 2009 at 6:26 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A couple of weeks ago, though, I took Molly&#8217;s advice: I boiled some kale. I toasted some bread. I fried an egg.</></>It was a cold night, and this was a soul-satisfying meal for such an evening. It was simple and filling. I won&#8217;t tell you the method, because Molly does a better job of interpreting Zuni than I could, but I will suggest you give it a try.</p>
    </div>

